From 55d9b5c03ccc5f8f640ec08e5fafe22ac2b3a2bc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: xuefenghao5121 <xuefenghao5121@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Apr 2026 01:33:20 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/6] DNN-Opt deep integration: replace ref_gemm with optimized
 GEMM backend

Integrate DNN-Opt as the FP32 GEMM backend for AArch64, replacing the
slow ref_gemm fallback in extended_sgemm(). This automatically
accelerates all code paths that call extended_sgemm: dnnl_sgemm(),
gemm_convolution_fwd_t, and gemm_f32_matmul_t.

Key changes:
- cmake/dnnopt.cmake: find and link libdnnopt_core.a
- cmake/options.cmake: add DNNL_AARCH64_USE_DNNOPT option
- dnnopt_gemm_wrapper.hpp: col-major to row-major duality adapter
  with safe ldc handling for dnnl_sgemm's internal M/N swap
- gemm.cpp: dispatch to dnnopt_sgemm before ref_gemm on AArch64

Performance vs vanilla ref_gemm (dnnl_sgemm, Neoverse N2):
  1-thread: 3.6-4.5x speedup (43.7 vs 9.8 GFLOPS at 1024^3)
  4-thread: 3.6x speedup (66.7 vs 18.8 GFLOPS at 1024^3)
  GEMM-conv: 1.1-1.3x speedup across ResNet layers

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
