Subject: [PATCH 4/6] gemm: add BRGEMM fallback using oneDNN's native JIT
 kernel

Add brgemm_sgemm_wrapper.hpp that uses oneDNN's brgemm (batched reduced
GEMM) as fallback for dnnl_sgemm on aarch64. No ACL dependency - uses
Xbyak_aarch64 JIT compiler.

Dispatch order:
1. dnnopt: all shapes (small-M optimized)
2. brgemm: fallback when dnnopt returns unimplemented
3. ref_gemm: slow reference implementation

Note: BRGEMM has JIT compilation overhead per call. Kernel caching
would improve performance for repeated calls to same shape.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
